        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 1:22PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 121 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Soddy-Daisy, or 11 miles north of Chattanooga. This thunderstorm was
nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chattanooga, Soddy-Daisy, Walden, Lakesite, Harrison, Fairmount, Red
Bank, North Chickamauga Creek Gorge, Harrison Bay State Park, and
Mowbray Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
